data.md:MetaData: PSV for the past 16 ka cal BP from Lake Tangra Yumco, Tibetan Plateau
The first high-resolution inclination record from the Tibetan Plateau for the past 16 ka cal BP - the Tangra Yumco record

Paleomagnetic data including inclination, declination, MAD values and MDF are given on an event correct composite depth (ECCD) and age for the composite lacustrine record TAN12-2 from Lake Tangra Yumco, Tibetan Plateau.
Independently dated paleomagnetic secular variation records from the Tibetan Plateau
